{{use dmy dates|date=July 2016}} {{infobox country at games | NOC = CAF | NOCname = Comité National Olympique et Sportif Centrafricain | games = Summer Olympics | year = 1992 | flagcaption = [[Flag of the Central African Republic]] | oldcode = | website = | location = [[Barcelona]] | competitors = 15 (13 men and 2 women) | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
The '''[[Central African Republic]]''' competed at the '''[[1992 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]]. Fifteen competitors, thirteen men and two women, took part in sixteen events in three sports.<ref name="SportsRef">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/CAF/summer/1992/ |title=Central African Republic at the 1992 Summer Games |accessdate=17 July 2016 |work=Sports Reference}}</ref>
==Athletics== {{main|Athletics at the 1992 Summer Olympics}}
'''Men's 100m metres''' *[[Valentin Ngbogo]] ** Heat &mdash; 10.79 (→ did not advance)
'''Men's 400m metres''' *[[Martial Biguet]] ** Heat &mdash; 47.82 (→ did not advance)
'''Men's 400m Hurdles''' *[[Jacques Henri Brunet]] ** Heat &mdash; 52.59 (→ did not advance)
'''Men's 5.000 metres''' *[[Ernest Ndissipou]] ** Heat &mdash; 14:40.12 (→ did not advance)
'''Men's Marathon''' * [[Ferdinand Amadi]] &mdash; 2:35.39 (→ 74th place)
'''Men's Discus Throw''' *[[Mickaël Conjungo]] ** Qualification &mdash; 57.46 m (→ did not advance)
'''Women's 800 metres''' *[[Brigitte Nganaye]] ** Heat &mdash; 2:15.70 (→ did not advance)
==Cycling== {{main|Cycling at the 1992 Summer Olympics}} Four male cyclists represented the Central African Republic in 1992.
;[[Cycling at the 1992 Summer Olympics – Men's individual road race|Men's road race]] * [[Vincent Gomgadja]] * [[Obed Ngaite]] * [[Christ Yarafa]]
;[[Cycling at the 1992 Summer Olympics – Men's team time trial|Men's team time trial]] * [[Rufin Molomadan]] * [[Vincent Gomgadja]] * [[Obed Ngaite]] * [[Christ Yarafa]]
