{{Infobox Stadium | stadium_name = Lokomotiv Stadium | nickname = | image = | fullname = | location = [[Tashkent]], [[Uzbekistan]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 11 May 2012 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Lokomotiv Tashkent]] | operator = [[Lokomotiv Tashkent]] | surface = | construction_cost = [[United States dollar|$]]18.1 million | architect = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor= | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = | tenants = [[Lokomotiv Tashkent]] | seating_capacity = 8,000 | dimensions = }}
'''Lokomotiv Stadium''', is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Tashkent]], [[Uzbekistan]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and is the home stadium of [[Lokomotiv Tashkent]].
The stadium was built on the site of [[Traktor Tashkent Stadium]]. The construction works started in 2009 and finished in 2012.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.anons.uz/article/other/502/|script-title=ru:Начато строительство нового стадиона «Локомотив»|publisher=anons.uz|date=2009-07-31|accessdate= |language=Russian}}</ref>The stadium holds 8,000 people.
The stadium was opened on 11 May 2012 with the [[2012 Uzbek League]] match between Lokomotiv and [[FK Andijan]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://pfl.uz/index.php?act=news&section=11&subsec=1&news_id=2769|title=«Локомотив»нинг янги стадиондаги илк ўйини дуранг билан якунланди|publisher=pfl.uz|date=2012-05-11|accessdate=2012-05-11|language=Uzbek}}</ref>
