'''Mohamed Aboker''' (born 4 June 1946) is a former [[middle-distance runner]] who competed for [[Somalia]].

Aboker was a member of [[Somalia|Somalia's]] first ever [[Summer Olympic]] team when he competed at the [[1972 Summer Olympics]] held in [[Munich]]. He was disqualified in the [[Athletics at the 1972 Summer Olympics – Men's 800 metres|800 metres]] but in the [[Athletics at the 1972 Summer Olympics – Men's 1500 metres|1500 metres]] he finished 10th in his heat, so not advancing to the next round.<ref>[https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ab/mohamed-aboker-1.html Sports Reference Profile]</ref>

